Categories: Detection -> Order Detection -> Incorrect Order Detection
Text Generation -> Command Execution -> Code Execution
Definition: In this task you will be given a string and you should find the longest substring that is a palindrome. A palindrome is a string that is the same backwards as it is forwards. If the shortest possible palindrome is length 1 you should return the first character.

Positive Examples.explanation: The substring 'gocog' is the longest possible substring that is also a palindrome. So this is a good example.
The longest palindrome is length 1 so the first character is returned. This is a good example.
The entire string 'ccpmpppppmpcc' is a palindrome, so the entire string is returned. This is a good example.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output is a palindrome but it is not a substring of the input. So this is a bad example.
The output is the length of the longest substring that is a palindrome, but not the substring itself. So this is a bad example.
The output is not a proper substring of the input. The first 'r' in does not appear directly before the first 'p' in the input string. So this is a bad example.
